{"id": 232079448, "title": "Bengaluru teenager electrocuted while plucking mangoes, younger brother injured", "text": "A teenage boy died after coming in contact with a live wire while plucking mangoes on the outskirts of Bengaluru on Sunday. The deceased has been identified as Sai Bhavani, 13, a resident of Sulibele village and a student of a pre-matric school in Hoskote. In the accident, the deceased\u2019s younger brother, 10, also sustained burn injuries. A police officer said Bhavani used a stick with a metal handle to pluck mangoes from a tree. \u201cHe came in contact with an 11 KV high-tension wire and died on the spot while his younger brother who was standing near him also sustained injuries,\u201d he added. The police have registered an Unnatural Death Report (UDR) in the case. Last week, a labourer, Bipul Kumar, 29, got electrocuted at an under-construction building site in Bengaluru\u2019s Kadugodi. The police, thereafter, arrested contractor Chenaram Kumawat under Section 304A (causing death by negligence) of the Indian Penal Code. The brother of the deceased had alleged that no proper safety measures were implemented by the contractor. Kumawat was later released on station bail.", "summary": "", "url": "https://indianexpress.com/article/cities/bangalore/bengaluru-teenager-electrocuted-while-plucking-mangoes-9382093/", "image": "https://images.indianexpress.com/2024/06/Left-to-right-2024-06-09T214553.231.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-09 16:17:42", "author": null, "language": "en", "catgory": "politics", "source_country": "in", "sentiment": -0.739}